# Residentas Services — public booking app
# Names only. Never commit real values.

# Public origin of THIS app. Used to build Stripe return URLs, so it must be the
# real origin in production or guests will be returned to the wrong place.
# Local: http://localhost:3002   Production: https://services.residentas.com
NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL=

# ---- Stripe (SERVER-ONLY) ----
# Two SEPARATE Stripe accounts, not Stripe Connect. Arco do Bandeira bookings
# are charged on the Residentas RMI account; every other property on Activos
# Reais. Never prefix any of these with NEXT_PUBLIC_.
STRIPE_SECRET_KEY_RMI=
STRIPE_SECRET_KEY_ACTIVOS_REAIS=

# Webhook signing secrets, one per account. Each webhook endpoint verifies
# signatures with its own account's secret.
#   /api/stripe/webhook/rmi            -> STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET_RMI
#   /api/stripe/webhook/activos-reais  -> STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET_ACTIVOS_REAIS
STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET_RMI=
STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET_ACTIVOS_REAIS=

# ---- Supabase ----
# Bookings are written ONLY by the Stripe webhook, using the service-role key.
# The service-role key bypasses RLS and must never reach the browser.
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=

# ---- Internal Guest Services API (SERVER-ONLY) ----
# Shared bearer token protecting /api/internal/guest-services/**, which the
# Central Hub staff portal consumes server-to-server. Must match
# GUEST_SERVICES_API_TOKEN in the Hub environment. Never prefix with
# NEXT_PUBLIC_ — that would publish it to every visitor of the booking site.
# These endpoints return guest contact details, so an unset value disables them
# (every request is rejected) rather than opening them up.
GUEST_SERVICES_API_TOKEN=

# NOTE: GUEST_SERVICES_BASE_URL is no longer used: pricing, checkout,
# persistence, webhooks and the internal staff API all run here.
